## User flow diagrams

### Registration
```
Step 1 (+ email) → Step 2 → Step 3 → Step 4 → Step 5 
  → [Create Clinic tap] → OTP sent to email 
  → OTP Verification Screen 
  → [OTP correct] → Clinic created → Auto-login → MainLayout
```

### Forgot Password
```
Login Screen → [Forgot Password?] → Forgot Password Screen (enter email)
  → [Send OTP] → OTP Verification Screen
  → [OTP correct] → Reset Password Screen (new password)
  → [Save] → Success → Back to Login
```

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated
- `dart analyze` on all modified files

### Manual
1. Register a new clinic with a real email → verify OTP email arrives → confirm it creates the clinic
2. Login with username+password → works as before
3. Tap "Forgot Password?" → enter registered email → OTP email arrives → verify → set new password → login with new password
4. Enter wrong OTP → see error, try again
5. Resend OTP after 60s cooldown

---

## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Have you configured SMTP in your PocketBase admin yet?** Without it, no OTP emails will send. Let me know what email provider you want to use (Gmail, SendGrid, Brevo, etc.) — I can help you set up the exact SMTP settings.

> [!NOTE]
> **PocketBase OTP duration**: Default is 5 minutes. That's generally fine — do you want it shorter or longer?
